## Enumerations

### enum  {#a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="enum WPDCheckMode ">
Mechanism to add runtime checking of devirtualization decisions, optionally trapping or falling back to indirect call on any that are not correct.

<EnumerationList title="Enumeration values">

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421ac9d3e887722f2bc482bcca9d41c512af" />
<EnumerationListItem name="None">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421a178e499decd0c21272bc34e4b3056eab" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Trap">

</EnumerationListItem>

<Link id="a0e65aef39009b683d7acb5884ae47421aad98505ec3c6cabbb406c37037410854" />
<EnumerationListItem name="Fallback">

</EnumerationListItem>

</EnumerationList>

Trapping mode is useful for debugging undefined behavior leading to failures with WPD. Fallback mode is useful for ensuring safety when whole program visibility may be compromised.

Definition at line <a href="#l00205">205</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/wholeprogramdevirt-cpp">WholeProgramDevirt.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>

### WholeProgramDevirtKeepUnreachableFunction {#a92e98b87a580ee2727a894cafc57a73e}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>cl::opt&lt; bool &gt; WholeProgramDevirtKeepUnreachableFunction(&quot;wholeprogramdevirt-keep-unreachable-function&quot;, cl::desc(&quot;Regard unreachable functions as possible devirtualize targets.&quot;), cl::Hidden, cl::init(true))</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
With Clang, a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor is emitted as a <code>llvm.trap</code> intrinsic followed by an unreachable IR instruction.

In the context of whole program devirtualization, the deleting destructor of a pure virtual class won&#39;t be invoked by the source code so safe to skip as a devirtualize target.

However, not all unreachable functions are safe to skip. In some cases, the program intends to run such functions and terminate, for instance, a unit test may run a death test. A non-test program might (or allowed to) invoke such functions to report failures (whether/when it&#39;s a good practice or not is a different topic).

This option is enabled to keep an unreachable function as a possible devirtualize target to conservatively keep the program behavior.

TODO: Make a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor precisely identifiable in Clang&#39;s codegen for more devirtualization in LLVM.

Definition at line <a href="#l00187">187</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/transforms/lib/transforms/ipo/wholeprogramdevirt-cpp">WholeProgramDevirt.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

This is needed to support legacy tests that don&#39;t contain !vcall&#95;visibility metadata (the mere presense of type tests previously implied hidden visibility).

<Link id="l00002" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00005" /><CodeLine lineNumber="5"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0 WITH LLVM-exception</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00006" /><CodeLine lineNumber="6"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00007" /><CodeLine lineNumber="7"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00008" /><CodeLine lineNumber="8"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00009" /><CodeLine lineNumber="9"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This pass implements whole program optimization of virtual calls in cases</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00010" /><CodeLine lineNumber="10"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// where we know (via !type metadata) that the list of callees is fixed. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00011" /><CodeLine lineNumber="11"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// includes the following:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00012" /><CodeLine lineNumber="12"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Single implementation devirtualization: if a virtual call has a single</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00013" /><CodeLine lineNumber="13"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   possible callee, replace all calls with a direct call to that callee.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00014" /><CodeLine lineNumber="14"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Virtual constant propagation: if the virtual function&#39;s return type is an</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00015" /><CodeLine lineNumber="15"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   integer &lt;=64 bits and all possible callees are readnone, for each class and</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00016" /><CodeLine lineNumber="16"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   each list of constant arguments: evaluate the function, store the return</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00017" /><CodeLine lineNumber="17"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   value alongside the virtual table, and rewrite each virtual call as a load</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00018" /><CodeLine lineNumber="18"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   from the virtual table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00019" /><CodeLine lineNumber="19"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Uniform return value optimization: if the conditions for virtual constant</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00020" /><CodeLine lineNumber="20"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   propagation hold and each function returns the same constant value, replace</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00021" /><CodeLine lineNumber="21"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   each virtual call with that constant.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00022" /><CodeLine lineNumber="22"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Unique return value optimization for i1 return values: if the conditions</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00023" /><CodeLine lineNumber="23"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   for virtual constant propagation hold and a single vtable&#39;s function</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00024" /><CodeLine lineNumber="24"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   returns 0, or a single vtable&#39;s function returns 1, replace each virtual</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00025" /><CodeLine lineNumber="25"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   call with a comparison of the vptr against that vtable&#39;s address.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00026" /><CodeLine lineNumber="26"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00027" /><CodeLine lineNumber="27"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// This pass is intended to be used during the regular and thin LTO pipelines:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00028" /><CodeLine lineNumber="28"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00029" /><CodeLine lineNumber="29"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// During regular LTO, the pass determines the best optimization for each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00030" /><CodeLine lineNumber="30"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// virtual call and applies the resolutions directly to virtual calls that are</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00031" /><CodeLine lineNumber="31"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// eligible for virtual call optimization (i.e. calls that use either of the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00032" /><CodeLine lineNumber="32"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// llvm.assume(llvm.type.test) or llvm.type.checked.load intrinsics).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00033" /><CodeLine lineNumber="33"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00034" /><CodeLine lineNumber="34"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// During hybrid Regular/ThinLTO, the pass operates in two phases:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00035" /><CodeLine lineNumber="35"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Export phase: this is run during the thin link over a single merged module</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00036" /><CodeLine lineNumber="36"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   that contains all vtables with !type metadata that participate in the link.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00037" /><CodeLine lineNumber="37"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   The pass computes a resolution for each virtual call and stores it in the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="38"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   type identifier summary.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="39"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Import phase: this is run during the thin backends over the individual</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="40"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   modules. The pass applies the resolutions previously computed during the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="41"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   import phase to each eligible virtual call.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="42"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="43"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// During ThinLTO, the pass operates in two phases:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="44"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Export phase: this is run during the thin link over the index which</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00045" /><CodeLine lineNumber="45"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   contains a summary of all vtables with !type metadata that participate in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="46"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   the link. It computes a resolution for each virtual call and stores it in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="47"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   the type identifier summary. Only single implementation devirtualization</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="48"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   is supported.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="49"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// - Import phase: (same as with hybrid case above).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00050" /><CodeLine lineNumber="50"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="51"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//===----------------------------------------------------------------------===//</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00169" /><CodeLine lineNumber="169"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00170" /><CodeLine lineNumber="170"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// With Clang, a pure virtual class&#39;s deleting destructor is emitted as a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00171" /><CodeLine lineNumber="171"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// &#96;llvm.trap&#96; intrinsic followed by an unreachable IR instruction. In the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00172" /><CodeLine lineNumber="172"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// context of whole program devirtualization, the deleting destructor of a pure</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00173" /><CodeLine lineNumber="173"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// virtual class won&#39;t be invoked by the source code so safe to skip as a</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00174" /><CodeLine lineNumber="174"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// devirtualize target.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00175" /><CodeLine lineNumber="175"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00176" /><CodeLine lineNumber="176"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// However, not all unreachable functions are safe to skip. In some cases, the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00177" /><CodeLine lineNumber="177"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// program intends to run such functions and terminate, for instance, a unit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00178" /><CodeLine lineNumber="178"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// test may run a death test. A non-test program might (or allowed to) invoke</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00249" /><CodeLine lineNumber="249"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// this aligns the used regions to start at MinByte.</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02038" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2038"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// test resolution, so that they aren&#39;t treated as Unsat and lowered to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02039" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2039"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// False, which will break any uses on assumes. Below we remove any type</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02040" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2040"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// test assumes that will not be treated as Unknown by LTT.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02041" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2041"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02042" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2042"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The type test assumes will be treated by LTT as Unsat if the type id is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02043" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2043"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// not used on a global (in which case it has no entry in the TypeIdMap).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02044" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2044"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (!TypeIdMap.count(TypeId))</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02046" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2046"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02047" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2047"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// For ThinLTO importing, we need to remove the type test assumes if this is</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02048" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2048"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// an MDString type id without a corresponding TypeIdSummary. Any</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02049" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2049"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// non-MDString type ids are ignored and treated as Unknown by LTT, so their</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02051" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2051"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// TypeIdSummary (e.g. because there was no use on a vcall, preventing the</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l02053" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2053"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Unsat by LTT and we need to remove its type test assumes here. If not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02054" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2054"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// used on a vcall we don&#39;t need them for later optimization use in any</span></CodeLine>
